APPROACH TOWARD FUNCTIONAL TEXT STRUCTURE ANALYSIS OF SCIENTIFIC ANDTECHNICAL DOCUMENTS.     A STRUCTURAL ANALYSIS OF TEXTS IS PRESENTED AS A PART OF A SEMANTIC METHOD FORREPRESENTING SCIENTIFIC AND TECHNICAL DOCUMENTS. 4 CONCEPTS OF THEME, METHOD,RESULT AND DISCUSSION ARE SELECTED AND A MODEL SET OF 'FUNCTIONAL PATTERNS'CONSISTING OF META-TERMS IN EACH SENTENCE OF THE ABSTRACT IS PREPARED. APRELIMINARY COMPUTER EXPERIMENT PRODUCED A PATTERN MATCHING PROCEDUREIDENTIFYING THE INFORMATION FUNCTION FOR EACH SENTENCE OF THE ABSTRACT BASEDON THE MODEL SET. THE RESULTS ARE EXAMINED AND DISCUSSED IN TERMS OFREPRODUCIBILITY OF THE MODEL SET AND EFFECTIVENESS OF THE PROCEDURE FOR THEOTHER DATA SETS